fields.description: Indicates the activity type the detected risk is linked to.  The possible values are: signin, servicePrincipal. Note that you must use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following value(s) in this evolvable enum: servicePrincipal.
fields.name: Activity

fields.description: Date and time when the risky activity occurred. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z
fields.name: ActivityDateTime

fields.description: Additional information associated with the risk detection. This string value is represented as a JSON object with the quotations escaped.
fields.name: AdditionalInfo

fields.description: The unique identifier for the associated application.
fields.name: AppId

fields.description: Correlation ID of the sign-in activity associated with the risk detection. This property is null if the risk detection is not associated with a sign-in activity.
fields.name: CorrelationId

fields.description: Date and time when the risk was detected. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.
fields.name: DetectedDateTime

fields.description: Timing of the detected risk , whether real-time or offline. The possible values are: notDefined, realtime, nearRealtime, offline, unknownFutureValue.
fields.name: DetectionTimingType

fields.description: Provides the IP address of the client from where the risk occurred.
fields.name: IPAddress

fields.description: The unique identifier for the key credential associated with the risk detection.
fields.name: KeyIds

fields.description: Date and time when the risk detection was last updated.
fields.name: LastUpdatedDateTime

fields.description: Location from where the sign-in was initiated.
fields.name: Location

fields.description: Request identifier of the sign-in activity associated with the risk detection. This property is null if the risk detection is not associated with a sign-in activity. Supports $filter (eq).
fields.name: RequestId

fields.description: Details of the detected risk. Note: Details for this property are only available for Workload Identities Premium customers. Events in tenants without this license will be returned hidden. The possible values are: none, hidden, adminConfirmedServicePrincipalCompromised, adminDismissedAllRiskForServicePrincipal. Note that you must use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following value(s) in this evolvable enum: adminConfirmedServicePrincipalCompromised , adminDismissedAllRiskForServicePrincipal.
fields.name: RiskDetail

fields.description: The type of risk event detected. The possible values are: investigationsThreatIntelligence, generic, adminConfirmedServicePrincipalCompromised, suspiciousSignins, leakedCredentials, anomalousServicePrincipalActivity, maliciousApplication, suspiciousApplication.
fields.name: RiskEventType

fields.description: Level of the detected risk. Note: Details for this property are only available for Workload Identities Premium customers. Events in tenants without this license will be returned hidden. The possible values are: low, medium, high, hidden, none.
fields.name: RiskLevel

fields.description: The state of a detected risky service principal or sign-in activity. The possible values are: none, dismissed, atRisk, confirmedCompromised.
fields.name: RiskState

fields.description: The display name for the service principal.
fields.name: ServicePrincipalDisplayName

fields.description: The unique identifier for the service principal. Supports $filter (eq).
fields.name: ServicePrincipalId

fields.description: Source of the risk detection. For example, identityProtection.
fields.name: Source

fields.description: Indicates the type of token issuer for the detected sign-in risk. The possible values are: AzureAD.
fields.name: TokenIssuerType
